Arcane Weapon
	KEY:Arcane Weapon ~ Magus
	CATEGORY:Special Ability
	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Supernatural
	DEFINE:MagusArcaneWeaponLVL|0
	DEFINE:MagusArcaneWeaponBonus|0
	DESC:You can imbue a melee weapon with powerful abilities. When you prepare your spells, you can also spend a portion of this time bonding with a single melee weapon. This grants the weapon a +%1 enhancement bonus. These bonuses can be added to the weapon, stacking with existing weapon enhancement to a maximum of +5, or they can be used be used to add any of the following weapon properties: dancing, flaming, flaming burst, frost, icy burst, keen, shock, shocking burst, speed, or vorpal. Adding these properties consumes an amount of bonus equal to the property's cost. These properties are added to any the weapon already has, but duplicates do not stack. If the weapon is not magical, at least a +1 enhancement bonus must be added before any other properties can be added. These bonuses and properties are decided when the weapon is bonded and cannot be changed until the next time the magus prepares spells. These bonuses do not function if the weapon is wielded by anyone other than the magus. Bonding with a weapon in this way is not without danger. A magus that is bonded to a weapon must have the weapon in hand to cast spells from the magus spell list; otherwise he must make a concentration check to cast such spells. The DC of this check is equal to 20 + the spell's level.|MagusArcaneWeaponBonus
	BONUS:VAR|MagusArcaneWeaponBonus|min(MagusArcaneWeaponLVL/4,20)
	SOURCEPAGE:p.5

